The paper proposes a space-efficient algorithm for computing a matrix decomposition of a transformed matrix, which is relevant to machine learning applications such as natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves error bounds and experiments, which suggest possible relevance to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
